HEADWORD: Specksioneer
<hw>Speck`sion*eer"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The chief
harpooner, who also directs in cutting up the speck, or blubber; -- so
called among whalers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

